column5: I would say it,s, lemon aid from lemons bud.  That looks like a sweet place to sit today.
Cigars, walleye, and cold beer looks fine to me
Cigars, walleye, and cold beer looks fine to me X2, although I might switch the beer for a Thermos full of Irish coffee
nice great way to spend a day
Sweet dude
You nabbed a walleye. Better then most of us today.
Ouch!  Looks like Hally got hit with a good dumping too!  Did you launch your boat with the bravo?

Great day for you, good going. A few more of those make a beauty pan fry. That must be diet Coke in those cans. I wonder if it's a coincidence all the folks I see open water fishing this winter don't have any grey whiskers? I remember casting onto patches of ice flow from Niagara to Nipp to Quinte and back. You pull the lure off them straight down. a killer technique. No grey then though. I'm happy to have grey hair, that means I still have some.
Awesome! Im waiting for my chance.
easier than launching a boat from sand... She must have glided nicely.  Desperation and deprivation will make ice fishermen do funny things
That's awesome!  Nice walleye too!
Nice way to spend New Years Chris !!!! Cheers man ?❄️?????
Yep, life is tough all over these days!!!
Not a thing wrong with that!!
Been thinking about doing the same thing Chris.  Cheers

Good report Chris! Some cold nights ahead of us in my area.  Things could be looking up.  I am getting pretty punchy to be honest.  Going up to my spot for another look Wednesday morning. But I'm not hopeful.....
LOL…great stuff Chris.
Some will be happy to hear there was a skim of ice about 200 yards out from shore this AM. -14C at 07:00 when I took the garbage out. I'm frozen, ya happy now
im glad all of this snow hit before the lock up...its way worse when you have 1 inch of ice and 2 feet of snow on it.
Hey, a fish was caught! I was hoping to do that at some point this december but never made it out!
